Guest Access Points & Staff Access Point: Guest and staff access through front doors
Access Times: Event dependant, check in with venue/client as to what time they have booked access from
Loading Bay:
Take Millennium Way to the end where Meriden Gate will be on your left. (when you come to a roundabout at the end take second left into Meriden Gate). https://w3w.co/trees.hotel.gangs 

When at Meriden Gate the security will ask where you are going and take registration details and check with the control room for access onto site. 

Once on site you will come to a mini roundabout, go left on the Red Tarmac Road and follow it all the way around keeping the Thames on your left and the Tent on your right. 

Continue driving until you can’t go any further, ie. Blue gate in front of you. Turn right into the compound and you have arrived at the back of indigo at The O2.

FCLs wont be able to stay onsite during the event. Check with venue ops manager if we can leave smaller vehicles/trader vehicles, it will depend from event to event so never assume you can.
Goods Lift / Stairs Only: Lift to Purple Lounge in downstairs concert hall
Cooking Restrictions: Frying permitted in BOH gazebo
Onsite Kitchen?: BOH gazebo which can be used, has access to hot/cold water, heat lamps. Space for 2-3 traders depending on set up
Cloakroom:
There is a cloakroom located in the reception area of the venue, hangers and rails are available in house, KERB would need to provide tags and staff. 

This cloakroom holds up to 300 items, the reception/merchandise desks can be used as an overspill for bags if it is not in use during the event. 

Alternatively, the cloakroom can be set up in the Purple room upstairs, depending on the event format and Client’s requirements
Waste Removal Info: KERB/traders to remove waste unless agreed otherwise with the venue (normally okay for small amounts of waste)
Power: To be sent to venue in advance
Water: Hot and cold water available in BOH gazebo
Venue Bar?:
Venue run and manages. KERB can provide tea/coffee/softs for conferences 

There is a long bar with drinking water taps, ice machine and fridges on the ground floor. The bar can be partially draped off for smaller events if needed and the rest of the bar used as BOH space. 

Tensa barriers for queue management can be requested from the venue team
Glassware: Images below  are of BOH gazebo (not bar)
Staff changing rooms/toilets/smoking are:
Smoking in loading bay area
Toilets in Purple Lounge upstairs and downstairs in main space
Fire Exit: Front doors, fire assembly point by Starbucks
Floor Restrictions?: Drugget for all traders including BOH

FOH power is supplied and distributed by the production team (make sure the client is aware of this).  This needs to be sent to the production team (who will then send it on to the venue to be checked).
Water:
Water access is in the BOH bar sink.  

Access through the door is #1234.  

 Waste water can be disposed of in the BOH bar sink.  

Washing up can be done in the BOH bar sink if the traders would like but not much space.
Venue Bar?:
KERB is able to provide bars at this venue.  

KERB to provide the bar, staff and stock.  

The venue can offer a bar for an event if the client would like at an additional cost to the venue hire.
Bar BOH Storage: BOH for KERB is in the BOH kitchen space.
Glassware:
Assume that no glass should be able to be used for events.  

All glassware should be polycarbs or vegware. All soft drinks and beers in bottles should be decanted to guests.  

Some exceptions are made for drinks receptions and glassware on the tables at seated dinners.  

If caterers or client happy to take on liability then the event can have glassware but for most events this should not be offered.
Site Restrictions:
There is a vehicle curfew in the loading bay / car park between 11pm - 8am.  

To get around this traders vehicles could park on the road outside the back of the Roundhouse and handball all equipment out of the space.
Room Hire / Rates & Capacities:
£27,500 + VAT   

Clients can hire the venue in 24 hour blocks starting from 10am, for a dry hire fee of £27,500+VAT. The 24 hour hire includes: 

Full use of the Main Space and other front of house areas 

Full use of all back of house areas including the service yard, kitchen marquee, x4 dressing rooms and a production office 

Lighting package (worth £8k) 

Sound package (worth £5k) 

20ft x 40ft stage 

Plant machinery 

High speed internet connection 

Water and power supply 

Technical support 

Dedicated Event Manager 

Duty Manager during event hours 

Medic during event hours 

24 hour housekeeping 

Seated dinner  - max 850   

Cabaret - max 650  

Standing - max 1800 (with stage & catering inside space)
Invoicing:
Invoice the client directly.  

KERB invoicing terms (unless otherwise agreed).
Staff changing rooms/toilets/smoking are:
Use of toilets or BOH kitchen space.  

Green Rooms at the back of the main space if required for acts. 

For guests this is outside the front of the venue. 

For all staff this is outside the BOH kitchen / next marquee.
Floor Restrictions?: Only height restriction in the space exists under the balcony  - 2.98m.

Notes:
EVENT MANAGER HAS A SEVERE AIRBORNE COCONUT ALLERGY - MUST NOTIFY PRE EVENT IF ANY COCONUT BASED PRODUCTS WILL BE ONSITE 

"As you may be aware, last summer we welcomed our Event Manager, Jess Porritt, to the Commercial Events team at Somerset House. Jess has a severe airborne allergy to coconut, which can cause anaphylaxis. Whilst she is confident managing this, and the relevant teams at Somerset House will be briefed on what to do in an emergency, we want to ensure we create a safe environment for her to work in.  

We would ask that moving forward if you can please inform us if you/your traders are using coconut in any part of an event menu, whether it is an element prepared on or off site. This should not affect the nature of your menus for clients, however if coconut or coconut based ingredients, oils, etc. are involved in a menu we will need to know with advance warning so that we can make necessary staffing adjustments on our side.  

This includes any foods or products which contain natural coconut, e.g. coconut dairy-substitute products or beauty products including coconut oil. Any synthetic coconut products are OK, such as coconut scented shampoo, but if in doubt or you have any other questions please check with our team.  

Please note that Jess, along with other members of our team, have other allergies not noted here, however these cause allergic reactions when ingested and are not airborne allergens. 

 We really appreciate your help with assisting us to create a safe environment for our team to work within and look forward to having you back on site for events soon."

Room Hire / Rates & Capacities:
The Embankment Galleries are available for hire from April to December 2026. The perfect space for larger receptions (up to 1,000), dinners (up to 340), conferences (up to 320), brand activations and fashion shows. Do get in touch with enquiries. 
We have availability in our Edmond J. Safra Fountain Court in September 2026 for bespoke events. Get in touch to find out more or if you have a client that might be interested!
In 2025 we launched Private View Receptions, refreshed conference, summer and festive packages, and the Moving Venue x Somerset House Summer Season 2026. 
We have recently launched an expanded wedding portfolio - which includes more detail on getting married at Somerset House, proposals at Somerset House, and wedding photography. If you have specialist wedding planners within your team, please do let us know — we’d love to discuss this offer in more detail and explore opportunities for cross-promotion.
We will once again have the stretch tent on our River Terrace, included as part of a client’s hire from 9 June to 3 July and 7 September to 4 October 2026.
We now have a page on our website dedicated to Exhibitions, Fairs and Special Projects, which is also where the brochure for these types of commercial hires can be found. Do share with clients where relevant and get in touch with us if you’d like any more information.
